</div>Well it does mean I feel less guilty buying a console version of the game.<br />
<br />
What it DOES do is allow them to do the microtransactions just like PSN/XBL for consoles except on PC.  Gaming is headed in that direction, sorry, hoss.  Do I agree or disagree?  I dunno, I am not sure I am the same gamer I was 5 years ago.  5 years ago, I would be up in arms about it.  Right now... I'm 28, and spending 5 bucks for maps so I can just click and go instead of downloading and finding good ones?  Ehhhh, I'm ok with that.<br />
<br />
I DO have issues with them preventing LAN play on any game - that was when the &quot;mods&quot; came out in force, for me.  I never played mods online, but when we had 8 of us in the same room... god the insanity was crazy, we'd have all sorts of stuff going on.</div>
