    <div align="left" id="post_message_489363">Well...technically you can still do that Psiko, but it might suck having 8 people trying to play off one connection. <br />
<br />
And I know the shift is toward micro transactions. I'm not necessarily unhappy about it, the real nickel and diming has yet to start, and some devs companies out there are being really reasonable about what they charge for, and what they offer for free. <br />
<br />
And if the end result means largely stable servers that can keep up with demand...that's good in my book too. Modded content and personalized servers are 'neat' (Christmas Crash), but personally I've never played a game where the mods dominated the stock content. I know that's true of HL2, and whether or not you prefer modded content is a subjective choice...but the majority play the stock content and that's it. <br />
<br />
I think Top actually put it best. He pirated CoD 4 but then went out and bought it because it was such an excellent game. I did the same thing, when someone shared it at a LAN party and I decided I wanted to play online.<br />
<br />
People will buy good games, regardless of how many extras they do or don't get.</div>
