<br />
Except they're not worried, at all. The chances of MW2 tanking financially because of this are about as good as the odds of you not flipping out over the next trivial slight a PC developer deals you. Hardcore PC gamers over inflate their own reaction to stuff, grumble and point the gnarly finger of dhoom and go kicking and screaming, all the way to checkout counter. Modded content and dedicated servers have always been a nice perk, but there's a significant portion of gamers out there who could care less about them.</div>
