</div>People are pissed as hell at Blizzard too, but Blizzard has two entirely different beasts of a game compared to CoD6. Besides Diablo II and StarCraft I, what else could people play other than the new ones? There's not much out there thats similar to them, well Diablo at least, that has the same kind of effort put into making an awesome game that Blizzard is no doubt putting into the new ones. CoD6 may be awesome, but it's just another FPS game in a sea of other FPS games. CoD4 MP was fun, but the lack of custom content for so long killed it for me and I went back to TF2 and never looked back and as far as I am concerned, TF2 is the king of FPS games in terms of how fun the game is.<br />
<br />
The game as a whole won't tank, because it has the console versions and a ton of idiots that will buy it up. As for there being a signification portion of gamers out there that don't care, that's horseshit and you know it. Those are two of the major reasons why PC gaming is miles ahead of console gaming and why people stick to it. If it weren't for modding, we wouldn't have two of the most popular games on the planet, Counter-Strike and Team Fortress. PC games have much longer lives due to the amount of maps and game play modes that users can concoct, and without them it is a straight up kick in the **** to PC gamers. And who the **** wouldn't want dedicated servers? Some moron who doesn't care about not having shitty ping's opinion is irrelevant when it comes to gaming, let alone the amount of stuff you cannot do without dedicated servers (league play, PUGs, clan servers, hell, clans in general). <br />
