</div>What do you mean by smaller stake?<br />
<br />
Regarding micro-charging, the free market will move to an equilibrium that will be frustrating to all - the balance will be just how much are gamers willing to pay for before they ditch the game- that will end them up paying and moaning about it, but not quite quitting.  The devs will feel like they are giving most of their work away for free and that they should be making more money for the content they produce, but they will be just willing to keep on doing it.<br />
<br />
At least, if I recall my one econ course from school correctly, it will go something like that.</div>
