    <div align="left" id="post_message_489436">Yes, I thought about the API, and suspect Bizzard might just be making available what they use themselves.<br />
<br />
If I'm managing that business, I would be thinking that releasing for public consumption as well as internal use probably drives a lot of beneficial behaviors on the team that develops the API, especially if they need a sense of product ownership that might be missing in a team that does not work on the game content per se.<br />
