</div>While I'm all for trying to find silver linings, since we ultimately don't have a choice in these matters...I think you're trying a little too hard there. And, personally, I don't think they are 'the same games.' The performance is different, the support levels are different and the amount of effort that's invested into a each version is different. <br />
<br />
Yet they still cost the same. Which means PC users, if the last crop of games are any indicator, will be paying higher cost for fewer options and the same problems (crashes, bugs, ect...), by virtue of the platform we play on. <br />
<br />
I'm concerned that, if the current trend continues, that PC ports will become even shittier than they are now. If PC gamers accept the higher price point, and effectively say &quot;Yes, we see the two versions as identical too,&quot; then PC developers have fewer reasons to go the extra mile with PC ports that we've, up until now, always enjoyed and expected. Game UIs have already shown that a lot of developers are content with &quot;just good enough for PC.&quot; And the shift to $60 PC titles, in the end, is rewarding them for that.</div>
