		<div align="left" style="font-size: 12px; color: #999999; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">I'm curious if you've even played the CoD games (either CoD4 or CoD WaW) on the consoles. They currently don't have dedicated servers for multiplayed on the consoles and I don't think I have EVER had a laggy game unless the host was about to drop. And if thats the case, you got booted back to the lobby and a new game restarted using another player as host within a few seconds. <br />
<br />
So what makes you think this is going to cause lag?</div>
		</td>
    <td width="30" align="center" valign="middle"><img src="/forums/images/closeq.gif" width="30" height="30" align="right"></td>
  </tr>
</table>
</div>No I haven't since I have enough sense to play stuff on the PC. You did read the part about where there is no choice as to who the host is, right? The game somehow magically makes the choice based on some criteria we haven't been told of, and if he drops the game pauses for five seconds while it figures out who the next host should be. Its also not just about the lag, they've gutted what made a PC game a PC game and just **** a console game out for us. 9vs9 is a huge change when the last game was 16vs16 for us. Also, do you even see ping in a numerical display on console games? Only things Ive seen on what few games Ive played have been some stupid cell phone-esque bar representation. <br />
<br />
And having played Borderlands on the PC online is enough for me to not want to touch non dedicated servers with a 10 foot pole, Ive had some good games, but Ive had a lot more games where I couldn't connect or it was laggy as balls, and thats only a four player game.<br />
<br />
