<br />
I understand that the PC platform has it's own unique challenges for the user, and I can understand the frustration that arises from having to deal with those challenges for the same experience (instead of a superior one, as was the case previously), but ultimately if the game has the same features on all platforms, shouldn't that mean they all have the same cost?<br />
<br />
I own both consoles and a gaming PC. I play games on all of them. I've had problems getting behind the outrage at the server changes in this case, since I don't understand how it causes a specific problem for players. But then I'm only peripherally involved in the discussions.</div>
