</div>Uh, yeah?  It's a business.  10 bucks for 5 maps ain't that bad, and 95% of the &quot;community&quot; maps sucked donkey balls anyway.  Sure, it sucks we don't have the option anymore - but will it REALLY be all that bad?  No, not really.<br />
<br />
Not all of us pirate EVERYTHING and then complain because they don't do things the way they want.  If I had pirated Borderlands, and then bitched about it, I'd be a hypocrite.  I paid for it, I am unhappy with parts of the PC version (it's so much fun I ignore the truly terrible things), so I complain about it.  Complaining about 9v9 with auto matchmaking and hosting...  without having tried it...  bite me.  It works fine for consoles - and if their service gets past routers, like a consoles, I think you won't even notice.  I'd almost bet you money they find who has the best ping to use as host - you will never end up playing Shadowcross cuz he's in Germany, but you might play me cuz I'm on a good high speed connection - I host all the time in Borderlands, cuz I know how to set up my ports.<br />
<br />
And no, using Borderlands is NOT a bad example - Gamespy is NOTHING like the matchmaking/autohosting you get on Consoles, Gamespy is archaic netcode, and a terrible service.  If Modern Warfare 2 is like THAT on PC?  Then yes, you have every right to be upset.  If it's like consoles are?  You'll be fine, quit yer bitchin'</div>
