</div>The loss of any modding is pretty shitty, even if the maps sucked. What if, god forbid, this starts a trend though? Modding is what keeps games alive long after they've been out and there's loads of maps out there for other games that are anything but shitty. Maps used to be released for free with free updates, like Valve still does, it wasn't till consoles came around (and mostly because of how MS does ****) that they started charging for major updates that included maps. <br />
